category.name: writing
description:
The Stockholm Writing Group is open to those who love to write. Especially those who feel compelled to write and probably have always written - articles, essays, books, manuscripts, blogs, speeches etc.

It doesn't matter what you are writing, we would love to have you in the group to share your ideas and give you support.

WE ARE NOT TEACHERS AND THIS IS NOT A CLASS! However, we do discuss elements of writing, play writing games, and give each other tips and constructive feedback if asked.

If you really want to learn how to write I recommend that you sign up for a course either online or in person. There are many online classes available to help get you started, you just have to look. Beware of expensive courses! They might be a scam. You can find many tips and tricks for FREE just by reading blogs written by writers.

Alexa

category.name: writing
description:
If you’re a dedicated writer of fiction, this group is for you. Together, we’ll explore what makes fiction work and how we can learn from published stories, covering everything from point-of-view to foreshadowing, and a million things in between. Our conversations may touch upon novels, but in most cases we’ll look at short stories, since they give us an opportunity to discuss beginnings, middles and endings without having to read hundreds of pages ahead of each meet-up. Reading will be distributed ahead of time, and you're expected to prepare ahead of the meetup. Please note that the meet-up will be in English and stories will be in English.

All you have to do is read the story and bring your notes, a willingness to share ideas and learn from others -- and, of course, your passion for writing fiction.
name: Copenhagen Creative Writing Meetup
organizer.name: Mathias

category.name: writing
description:
Please RSPV only if you will actually join. If for whatever reason you won't come, please let us know!

"The Bloomsbury Group was a group of associated English writers, intellectuals, philosophers and artists, the best known members of which included Virginia Woolf[...] Their works and outlook deeply influenced literature, aesthetics, criticism, and economics as well as liberal and permissive attitudes towards feminism, pacifism, and sexuality."

"Slotsholmen is an island in the harbour of Copenhagen, Denmark, and part of Copenhagen Inner City. The name is taken from the successive castles and palaces located on the island since Bishop Absalon constructed the city's first castle on the island in 1167 at the site where Christiansborg Palace lies today."

As the Bloomsbury Group takes his name from the area of London, I decided to pick an area in Copenhagen where we could meet and share everything that crosses our minds.
My idea with this group is to gather people and share thoughts about literature, art, philosophy, share our creativity and passions, and of course, having fun.This group is still an idea in process, and I would be more than glad if you people interested in it, could help me grow this idea into something concrete. Feel free to share your thoughts!
name: The Slotsholmen Group
organizer.name: Alex Sandoni

category.name: writing
description:
The Stockholm Writing Group is open to those who love to write. Especially those who feel compelled to write and probably have always written - articles, essays, books, manuscripts, blogs, speeches etc.

It doesn't matter what you are writing, we would love to have you in the group to share your ideas and give you support.

WE ARE NOT TEACHERS AND THIS IS NOT A CLASS! However, we do discuss elements of writing, play writing games, and give each other tips and constructive feedback if asked.

If you really want to learn how to write I recommend that you sign up for a course either online or in person. There are many online classes available to help get you started, you just have to look. Beware of expensive courses! They might be a scam. You can find many tips and tricks for FREE just by reading blogs written by writers.

Alexa

category.name: writing
description:
If you’re a dedicated writer of fiction, this group is for you. Together, we’ll explore what makes fiction work and how we can learn from published stories, covering everything from point-of-view to foreshadowing, and a million things in between. Our conversations may touch upon novels, but in most cases we’ll look at short stories, since they give us an opportunity to discuss beginnings, middles and endings without having to read hundreds of pages ahead of each meet-up. Reading will be distributed ahead of time, and you're expected to prepare ahead of the meetup. Please note that the meet-up will be in English and stories will be in English.

All you have to do is read the story and bring your notes, a willingness to share ideas and learn from others -- and, of course, your passion for writing fiction.
name: Copenhagen Creative Writing Meetup
organizer.name: Mathias

category.name: writing
description:
Please RSPV only if you will actually join. If for whatever reason you won't come, please let us know!

"The Bloomsbury Group was a group of associated English writers, intellectuals, philosophers and artists, the best known members of which included Virginia Woolf[...] Their works and outlook deeply influenced literature, aesthetics, criticism, and economics as well as liberal and permissive attitudes towards feminism, pacifism, and sexuality."

"Slotsholmen is an island in the harbour of Copenhagen, Denmark, and part of Copenhagen Inner City. The name is taken from the successive castles and palaces located on the island since Bishop Absalon constructed the city's first castle on the island in 1167 at the site where Christiansborg Palace lies today."

As the Bloomsbury Group takes his name from the area of London, I decided to pick an area in Copenhagen where we could meet and share everything that crosses our minds.
My idea with this group is to gather people and share thoughts about literature, art, philosophy, share our creativity and passions, and of course, having fun.This group is still an idea in process, and I would be more than glad if you people interested in it, could help me grow this idea into something concrete. Feel free to share your thoughts!
name: The Slotsholmen Group
organizer.name: Alex Sandoni

description:

Denna grupp är till för dig som är amatörskribent - oavsett om du aldrig någonsin skrivit en längre text eller jobbat ihop flertal noveller genom åren - och söker inspiration, motivation eller bara en ursäkt att komma igång. category.name: writing
description:
If you’re a dedicated writer of fiction, this group is for you. Together, we’ll explore what makes fiction work and how we can learn from published stories, covering everything from point-of-view to foreshadowing, and a million things in between. Our conversations may touch upon novels, but in most cases we’ll look at short stories, since they give us an opportunity to discuss beginnings, middles and endings without having to read hundreds of pages ahead of each meet-up. Reading will be distributed ahead of time, and you're expected to prepare ahead of the meetup. Please note that the meet-up will be in English and stories will be in English.

All you have to do is read the story and bring your notes, a willingness to share ideas and learn from others -- and, of course, your passion for writing fiction.

category.name: writing
description:
Please RSPV only if you will actually join. If for whatever reason you won't come, please let us know!

"The Bloomsbury Group was a group of associated English writers, intellectuals, philosophers and artists, the best known members of which included Virginia Woolf[...] Their works and outlook deeply influenced literature, aesthetics, criticism, and economics as well as liberal and permissive attitudes towards feminism, pacifism, and sexuality."

"Slotsholmen is an island in the harbour of Copenhagen, Denmark, and part of Copenhagen Inner City. The name is taken from the successive castles and palaces located on the island since Bishop Absalon constructed the city's first castle on the island in 1167 at the site where Christiansborg Palace lies today."

As the Bloomsbury Group takes his name from the area of London, I decided to pick an area in Copenhagen where we could meet and share everything that crosses our minds.
My idea with this group is to gather people and share thoughts about literature, art, philosophy, share our creativity and passions, and of course, having fun.This group is still an idea in process, and I would be more than glad if you people interested in it, could help me grow this idea into something concrete. Feel free to share your thoughts!
name: The Slotsholmen Group

description:
Hej,
Denna grupp är till för dig som är amatörskribent - oavsett om du aldrig någonsin skrivit en längre text eller jobbat ihop flertal noveller genom åren - och söker inspiration, motivation eller bara en ursäkt att komma igång. Vi sätter agendan, och tider då vi möts baseras till en början efter vår kalender. Det är viktigt att ingen känner press eller stress. Tanken är att vi ska hitta övningar som inspirerar och vi stöttar varandra i skrivandet.

category.name: writing
description:
The Stockholm Writing Group is open to those who love to write. Especially those who feel compelled to write and probably have always written - articles, essays, books, manuscripts, blogs, speeches etc.

It doesn't matter what you are writing, we would love to have you in the group to share your ideas and give you support.

WE ARE NOT TEACHERS AND THIS IS NOT A CLASS! However, we do discuss elements of writing, play writing games, and give each other tips and constructive feedback if asked.

If you really want to learn how to write I recommend that you sign up for a course either online or in person. There are many online classes available to help get you started, you just have to look. Beware of expensive courses! They might be a scam. You can find many tips and tricks for FREE just by reading blogs written by writers.

category.name: writing
description:
The Stockholm Writing Group is open to those who love to write. Especially those who feel compelled to write and probably have always written - articles, essays, books, manuscripts, blogs, speeches etc.

It doesn't matter what you are writing, we would love to have you in the group to share your ideas and give you support.

WE ARE NOT TEACHERS AND THIS IS NOT A CLASS! However, we do discuss elements of writing, play writing games, and give each other tips and constructive feedback if asked.

If you really want to learn how to write I recommend that you sign up for a course either online or in person. There are many online classes available to help get you started, you just have to look. Beware of expensive courses! They might be a scam. You can find many tips and tricks for FREE just by reading blogs written by writers.

category.name: writing
description:
If you’re a dedicated writer of fiction, this group is for you. Together, we’ll explore what makes fiction work and how we can learn from published stories, covering everything from point-of-view to foreshadowing, and a million things in between. Our conversations may touch upon novels, but in most cases we’ll look at short stories, since they give us an opportunity to discuss beginnings, middles and endings without having to read hundreds of pages ahead of each meet-up. Reading will be distributed ahead of time, and you're expected to prepare ahead of the meetup. Please note that the meet-up will be in English and stories will be in English.

All you have to do is read the story and bring your notes, a willingness to share ideas and learn from others -- and, of course, your passion for writing fiction.
name: Copenhagen Creative Writing Meetup

category.name: writing
description:
Please RSPV only if you will actually join. If for whatever reason you won't come, please let us know!

"The Bloomsbury Group was a group of associated English writers, intellectuals, philosophers and artists, the best known members of which included Virginia Woolf[...] Their works and outlook deeply influenced literature, aesthetics, criticism, and economics as well as liberal and permissive attitudes towards feminism, pacifism, and sexuality."

"Slotsholmen is an island in the harbour of Copenhagen, Denmark, and part of Copenhagen Inner City. The name is taken from the successive castles and palaces located on the island since Bishop Absalon constructed the city's first castle on the island in 1167 at the site where Christiansborg Palace lies today."

As the Bloomsbury Group takes his name from the area of London, I decided to pick an area in Copenhagen where we could meet and share everything that crosses our minds.
My idea with this group is to gather people and share thoughts about literature, art, philosophy, share our creativity and passions, and of course, having fun.This group is still an idea in process, and I would be more than glad if you people interested in it, could help me grow this idea into something concrete. Feel free to share your thoughts!
name: The Slotsholmen Group
organizer.name: Alex Sandoni
